    "plan_content": "## Plan Summary\n\nHere's what I found and what the plan covers:\n\n### Codebase findings\n- **No existing geo code** anywhere in `packages/next/src/` — clean slate\n- The `next/server` pattern is the exact template to follow: a `.ts` implementation in `spec-extension/`, a `.js` CommonJS entry, and a `.d.ts` declarations file\n- `packages/next/package.json` has a `\"files\"` array with paired `.js`/`.d.ts` entries; `geo.js`/`geo.d.ts` slots in alphabetically after `form.js`/`form.d.ts` (lines 42–43)\n\n### 5 files to create/modify\n\n| # | File | Action |\n|---|------|--------|\n| 1 | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts` | **Create** — exports `Geo` interface + 4 functions |\n| 2 | `packages/next/geo.js` | **Create** — CommonJS entry (`require('next/dist/...')`) |\n| 3 | `packages/next/geo.d.ts` | **Create** — re-exports all types and functions |\n| 4 | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts` | **Create** — 8 test cases using `assert` |\n| 5 | `packages/next/package.json` | **Edit** — add `\"geo.js\"`, `\"geo.d.ts\"` to `files` array |\n\n### Key implementation decisions\n- `headers.get()` returns `null` → `?? undefined` converts to satisfy TypeScript optional fields\n- `cf-ipcountry` (Cloudflare) is a fallback for `countryCode` when the Vercel header is absent\n- `country` (full name) derived from `countryCode` via a `COUNTRY_NAMES` map (10 entries)\n- Haversine formula for `geoDistance` with Earth radius = 6371 km\n- `isInRegion` uses `.toLowerCase()` on both sides for case-insensitive comparison\n- Tests use Node.js built-in `assert` — no external framework",
